Cancellation of Subscription:


The user opens the Google Play Store app on their device.
They click on the icon with three lines in the top left corner to open the side menu.
Select the "Subscriptions" option from the menu.
A list of all active subscriptions of the user will be displayed. The user finds the subscription they wish to cancel and clicks on it.
Then they click on the "Cancel subscription" option and follow the instructions to confirm the cancellation.
Cancellation done on Time:
Subscription cancellation must be done at least 24 hours before the current subscription period expires to avoid automatic renewal and charges for the next period.
No Refund Policy:

Fees for subscriptions that have already been charged will not be refunded to users after canceling the subscription. After canceling the subscription, the user will still have access to subscription content until the end of the current billing period.
Additional Assistance:

For additional assistance or questions regarding subscription cancellation, users can contact our customer support through the contact form on our website or via the email address provided in the contact information.
